        <section name="Introduction">
            The Java Pairing Based Cryptography Library (jPBC) provides:
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        A <a href="./docs/pairing.html">Java Port</a> of the
                        <a href="http://crypto.stanford.edu/pbc/">Pairing-Based Cryptography Library (PBC)</a>
                        library developed by <a href="http://crypto.stanford.edu/~blynn/">Ben Lynn</a>.
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        A
                        <a href="./docs/pbcwrapper.html">
                            Java Wrapper
                        </a>
                        around the
                        <a href="http://crypto.stanford.edu/pbc/">PBC</a>
                        library. The wrapper provides a tiny and efficient layer
                        to enable the communication between PBC and jPBC.
                        The pairing computation can be then
                        directly delegated to PBC resulting in improved performance.
                    </p>
                </li>

                <li>
                    <p>
                        <a href="./docs/multimaps.html">
                            Practical Multilinear Maps over the Integer
                        </a>
                        with full multi-thread support.
                    </p>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </section>

